def: Of or pertaining to billows; swelling or swollen into largewaves; full of billows or surges; resembling billows.And whitening down the many-tinctured stream, Descends the billowyfoam. Thomson.
An instrument or machine for measuring work done, especiallyfor ascertaining the number of rotations made by a machine or wheelin manufacturing cloth; a counter. Ure.
A genus of extinct Merostomata, found in Silurian rocks. Someof the species are more than three feet long.
Pertaining to, or resembling, an order of plants like thepalms, but having exogenous wood. The sago palm is an example.
Pertaining to, or formed by, intersections.
The wax-covered fruit of the wax myrtle, or bayberry. SeeBayberry, and Candleberry tree.

Penetrating rays readily deflected by a magnetic or electricfield, emitted by radioactive substances, as radium. They consist ofnegatively charged particles or electrons, apparently the same inkind as those of the cathode rays, but having much higher velocities(about 35,000 to 180,000 miles per second).
Of or pertaining to Asia; Asiatic. "Asian princes." Jer.Taylor.-- n.
An arrow without a barb, for shooting at butts; an arrow. [Alsobut shaft.] Shak.
